data.text: @sugan2424 @TwitterDev @threadreaderapp You have TweetDeck for that, you can load up your twitter lists in different columns and keep track of live updates.

@TwitterDev What kind of tweet / attachment is this?
It looks like a poll with an image but the buttons allow you to create a new, slightly different tweet based on what you choose. The API returns no attachments - but the tweet has pre-populated tweet buttons. https://t.co/PCaEj7KRWi

• Thirdly, that @Twitter, @Twittersafety, @Twitterdev, and @jack, et. al. have done a pretty good thing by showing the restraint to simply *inform* the userbase of the presence of hacking "down the line", rather than squash it AS a spectre.
